## THE FIVE UNBREAKABLE BUILD RULES

RULE 1 — CONFIG FIRST.
Every component reads from productConfig before it renders anything.
Zero hardcoded product names, labels, colors, or feature flags anywhere in component code.
If you are about to hardcode the word "Catering", "GridMaster", a hex color, or a nav label
inside a component — STOP. Read it from productConfig instead.

RULE 2 — SCHEMA BEFORE SCREENS.
The full Supabase schema (v1.0 + Patch v2.0) must be applied before writing any screen.
Do not invent table or column names. Use only what is defined in the schema documents.

RULE 3 — SHARED COMPONENTS ARE BUILT ONCE.
If a component is marked SHARED, it lives in src/components/shared/ and is never rebuilt.
Do not create a duplicate version of a shared component inside a page or feature folder.
If you need a shared component and it doesn't exist yet, build it in shared/ first.

RULE 4 — TEST EACH PHASE BEFORE MOVING TO THE NEXT.
Do not scaffold the next screen until the current one passes its defined test criteria.

RULE 5 — .cursorrules IS ACTIVE.
You are reading these rules. They govern every file you create, every component you write,
every Supabase query you generate. When in doubt, refer back here.

