## LANGUAGE RULES — NON-NEGOTIABLE

These terms are BANNED. If you write them, delete them immediately:
  - "clock in" → always "check in"
  - "clock out" → always "check out"
  - "hours logged" → always "times logged"
  - "dashboard" → always "Command Center"
  - "Save the Date" (for staff responses) → always "Interest List"
  - "clock-out code" → always "check-out code"

These terms are REQUIRED:
  - "Command Center" — not dashboard, not home screen, not overview
  - "check in" / "check out" — always two words when used as a verb
  - "Estimated Hours" — staff portal only, labeled as estimate, never as payroll hours
  - "Interest List" — official platform language for staff pre-commitment responses

NEVER reference payroll, pay rates, or payment processing in any staff-facing screen.

