## PRODUCTCONFIG STRUCTURE

productConfig is the single source of truth for all product-level customization.
Every component that renders a label, color, feature flag, or nav item reads from it.

Required top-level keys:
  product_type       — "catering" | "vending" | "gigs" | "venues" | "services"
  product_name       — display name, e.g. "Catering"
  brand_name         — always "GridMaster HQ"
  trial_days         — 45 for Catering and Vending; 30 for Gigs
  navigation         — array of nav items per sidebar (red/blue)
  features           — feature flags object
  labels             — overridable label map (e.g. "Command Center", "Coordinator")
  colors             — Tailwind class overrides if product-specific
  roles              — ordered list of roles available in this product
  sms_keywords       — full keyword list
  pricing            — tier definitions

Catering-specific config keys:
  event_types        — array with label, color bar hex, and calendar display properties
  grid_departments   — FOH | BOH | Setup/Breakdown | Other
  standard_roles     — server, bartender, bar_back, food_runner, captain, setup_crew,
                       line_cook, prep_cook, dishwasher, kitchen_runner
  rating_floors      — 1–4 star tap UI configuration
  buffer_options     — [0, 5, 10, 15, 20] — coordinator actively chooses, no default
  certifications     — TIPS, ServSafe, food handler, custom

