## SUPABASE RULES

organization_id appears on EVERY table without exception.
Every query filters by organization_id — no exceptions.
Phone number is the primary key for all staff records.
All tables include created_at and updated_at (auto-managed by Supabase).
Soft deletes only — archived records are never hard-deleted.
Row Level Security is enabled on every table.
Use Supabase RLS policies — never bypass with service_role key in frontend code.
The service_role key never goes in frontend code or the .env VITE_ namespace.

Table names to use (do not invent new ones):
  organizations, users, staff, staff_roles, staff_certifications, staff_availability,
  clients, client_locations, events, event_sections, event_grid_rows,
  event_staff_assignments, outreach_messages, staff_responses, ratings, check_ins,
  check_outs, temp_agencies, temp_agency_requests, temp_agency_rosters,
  invoice_reconciliations, sos_incidents, competing_events, sms_keywords,
  training_tips, (plus all Patch v2.0 additions)

