## CANCELLATION & POSTPONEMENT

Cancelled event pill: black background, white text, event name only, no time.
Cancelled events: hidden by default behind "Show Cancelled" toggle (off by default).
Cancellation flow: coordinator taps event → Cancel Event → confirmation prompt →
  fires on confirm. Confirmation text: "This will release all confirmed staff and
  cannot be undone. Continue?"
Cancellation priority flag: 14 days for all cancellation types including force majeure.
Priority flag badge: "Recently cancelled" — visible to coordinator only.
Flag expires at 14 days OR when staff works their next event, whichever comes first.

Postponed event pill: black background, white text, reads "postponed · hold".
Shown at original date until new date confirmed.
Postponement staff SMS: "[Company]: [Event Name] has been moved to [New Date].
  Can you still make it? Reply YES or NO."
Response window: 48 hours. Follow-up SMS requires coordinator approval before sending.

Emergency Cancel: red button inside event — separate from standard Cancel Event.
One tap, fires immediately, no confirmation delay.
Emergency Postpone option available on same Emergency Cancel screen.

