## COMMON VIOLATIONS TO AVOID

These are the most common Cursor mistakes on this project. Watch for them.

VIOLATION: Hardcoding "Catering" or "GridMaster" inside a component.
  FIX: productConfig.product_name and productConfig.brand_name.

VIOLATION: Hardcoding a hex color inside a component.
  FIX: Use Tailwind classes mapped to the brand token system.

VIOLATION: Using "dashboard" anywhere in UI text.
  FIX: "Command Center".

VIOLATION: Using "clock in" or "clock out" anywhere.
  FIX: "check in" / "check out".

VIOLATION: Using "hours logged".
  FIX: "times logged".

VIOLATION: Building a shared component inside a page or feature folder.
  FIX: Move it to src/components/shared/ immediately.

VIOLATION: Rebuilding a shared component when one already exists.
  FIX: Import from src/components/shared/. Never duplicate.

VIOLATION: Writing a Supabase query without filtering by organization_id.
  FIX: Every query includes .eq('organization_id', orgId).

VIOLATION: Using the Supabase service_role key in any frontend code.
  FIX: Use only the anon key (VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY). RLS handles access control.

VIOLATION: Auto-publishing an AI suggestion or automated change without coordinator approval.
  FIX: Flag and prompt. Option B is always the default.

VIOLATION: Displaying star ratings to staff.
  FIX: Ratings are internal. Never shown in staff-facing screens.

VIOLATION: Allowing a zero-star rating submission.
  FIX: Minimum 1 star. RatingStarSelector must enforce this.

VIOLATION: Referencing payroll, pay rates, or payment in any staff-facing screen.
  FIX: Remove entirely. Label hours as "Estimated Hours" and add "Estimated" qualifier.

VIOLATION: Allowing hard delete on any record.
  FIX: Soft delete only. Set is_archived = true or equivalent. Never DELETE from Supabase.

VIOLATION: Building a nav item that is hardcoded.
  FIX: All nav items come from productConfig.navigation.

